31.title: Episode #3.31
31.plot: After a few hours, Grachi and Axel return to the present: they actually spent six months in 1888 and are now dating, upsetting Daniel. Diego tries to find the secret library of the Magic School with the help of Amaya.

32.title: Episode #3.32
32.plot: Daniel is jealous of Grachi and Axel. Mía tries to seduce Daniel, but he tells her that at the moment they can only be friends. Amaya and Diego find the secret library.

33.title: Episode #3.33
33.plot: Daniel doesn't want to give up on Grachi. Amaya is caught with the books from the secret library and her father forbids her to see Diego again. Manu finds out that Mecha is his Guardian.

34.title: Episode #3.34
34.plot: Amaya tells Diego she hates Kanays, and he decides to leave and search for Kim. Silvia, Lucia, Katty, Dotty, Carlos and Sebastián try to steal the answers of the maths test, but Francisco and Úrsula hear a noise and begin to investigate.

35.title: Episode #3.35
35.plot: Francisco and Úrsula find Katty and Dotty, but Úrsula tells Francisco she called them. Mía asks Grachi to stay away from Daniel.

imdb.plot outline: "Grachi" follows the story of Graciela "Grachi" Alonso (Isabella Castillo), who just happens to be a witch that moves to a new city. She experiences love for the first time while dating Daniel Esquivel (Andrés Mercado) and meeting BFF Mercedes "Mecha" Estevez (Sol Rodríguez), Matilda Roman (Kimberly Dos Ramos), The Red Panthers, Mía Novoa (María Gabriela de Faría), Diego Forlan (Rafael de la Feunte) and Axel Vélez (Danilo Carrera) and realizing that life has its ups and downs and learning to experience everything coming her way.

plot: Graciela "_Grachi_ (qv)" Alonso just happens to be a witch who moves to a new city. She experiences love for the first time while dating Daniel.

"_Grachi_ (qv)" follows the story of Graciela "_Grachi_ (qv)" Alonso (Isabella Castillo), who just happens to be a witch that moves to a new city. She experiences love for the first time while dating Daniel Esquivel (Andrés Mercado) and meeting BFF Mercedes "Mecha" Estevez (Sol Rodríguez), Matilda Roman (Kimberly Dos Ramos), The Red Panthers, Mía Novoa (María Gabriela de Faría), Diego Forlan (Rafael de la Feunte) and Axel Vélez (Danilo Carrera) and realizing that life has its ups and downs and learning to experience everything coming her way.

Fifteen-year-old Graciela '_Grachi_ (qv)' Alonso moves to another town with her father Francisco. Here she meets new friends (including Mecha, who becomes her best friend) and her first love, Daniel. Matilda, Daniel's girlfriend and _Grachi_ (qv)'s neighbor, doesn't look kindly on the relationship between the boy and _Grachi_ (qv), and, when she finds out she's a witch, decides to hinder her rival; but the new girl herself has magical powers, inherited from her late mum, and is the most powerful witch in history. The first season focuses on the struggle for Daniel and the school principal's plan to absorb the powers of the two young witches and steal the magical book Exoren; the second season sees _Grachi_ (qv) facing Mía, a wicked witch her age who wants Daniel. In the third and last season _Grachi_ (qv) begins to attend the school of witchcraft, where she meets the wizard Axel, with whom she shares dreams about a mysterious necklace.::Elisa Forcellini
